Show_spots

The function show_spots plots the the spots found on every sample included in a matisse object. It can plot both spots or clustered cells.
Input: Matisse (MatisseMOD) object
Output: Images/figures showing the expression of each gene/ distrubition of each cell type

Example

Here you have the example of how to use the function. First we load the data
load ('data\Matisse objects\Spots_mousebrain.mat');
Then we just call the function giving as an input a matisse object. NOTE THAT: This function will use the information in Matisse.spotname as gene name / cell name
show_spots(SPOTS)
